As far as the &quot;cryptic&quot; patch messages.  That shit appeals to probably 5% of the gaming community.  Not to mention the ratio of shit they actually patch and what they put in the patch message even &quot;cryptically&quot; is about 10:1.  <br>
<br>
If they feel they'd be ruining our gaming experience by telling us wtf is in the patches, then they could add a disclaimer button that reads, &quot;yes I want to see what you changed&quot; after patches so the other 95% of us who want to know what we should expect to be broken can be prepaired.  <br>
